    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-01-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23,
                                1897</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Feb. 8.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 251.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: From interviews had this day by myself
                            with Privy Councillor Wermuth, of the Imperial home office, and by Mr.
                            Jackson with his excellency Dr. von Boetticher, the head of that office,
                            I am informed that the pending applications of the American insurance
                            companies for readmission to Prussia, together with the accompanying
                            papers submitted by the companies, and the reports of the experts, etc.,
                            are now before the Prussian ministry of state, of which Dr. von
                            Boetticher is the vice-president, and that it is expected very soon to
                            have the question made the order of the day, so that a final decision in
                            regard to it may be made.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
